body_text:
Fix clang_version does not expand as expected. This fix is sub-product of previous curl compression patch (#1550).
One can verify the correctness of the patch from the following snippet
#!/bin/bash

fxy() {
    echo "${1#v}" and "${2#v}"
}

g() {
    echo "h"
}

echo $(fxy g h)
echo $(fxy "$(g)" h)

Fixes #2367.
I expect this to be more robust than before, since it only considers the names of environment variables, not their values.
@ljharb Should we try to reproduce #2360 to test for regressions?
